{"TopicId":145972,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"[Request] Advanced Heat Shield","CreatedByName":"elpollodiablo","CreatedById":128492,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-15T13:05:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"elpollodiablo","CreatedById":128492,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-15T13:05:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried many times to do it with wings, robotics, welding and some .cfg editing. It kind of works, but just looks terrible and the wing clipping tends to produce eye cancer effects.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know if this may actually work as a mod, but my lack of knowledge of models and how to animate them is the reason for asking.. so: Would someone be interested in creating a more advanced heat shield that can retract the innermost 1/10, allowing the engines to fire?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIm obviously talking about the \u0022Pegasus\u0022 from BBC\u0027s \u0022Voyage to the Stars\u0022:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022097310c3a55dc2ab50d98f614d058183cbeefc8f\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.bbc.co.uk/staticarchive/097310c3a55dc2ab50d98f614d058183cbeefc8f.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t have to be a Replica at all, im just looking for that functionality.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sebi.zzr","CreatedById":81294,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-17T16:08:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/128492-elpollodiablo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022128492\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/128492-elpollodiablo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@elpollodiablo\u003C/a\u003E,\u003C/span\u003Eyou might check \u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbal.curseforge.com/projects/project-icarus/files/2221344\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ELH_Icarus\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0from \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/12078-025-lionhead-aerospace-inc-icarus-v04-updated/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ELionhead Aerospace Inc.\u003C/a\u003E.Maybe it would need some *.cfg tweaks,but in basics work in KSP 1.1.3\u003Cbr\u003E\nVideo:\u003Ca href=\u0022http://sendvid.com/1ztlghd0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://sendvid.com/1ztlghd0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"elpollodiablo","CreatedById":128492,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-17T18:42:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is perfect! It needs some tweaks indeed, at least with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E it\u0027s also a very heavy parachute and it has no ablators, but otherwise, just what the doctor ordered. Amazing i never found this mod, thank you very much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Qwarkk","CreatedById":154770,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-18T00:25:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was looking for something similar to this not too long ago - this is great.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a simple way to edit the size of the central hole?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sebi.zzr","CreatedById":81294,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-19T08:31:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222720706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145972\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471479924\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154770\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Qwarkk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E18\u200E.\u200E8\u200E.\u200E2016 at 2:25 AM, Qwarkk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a simple way to edit the size of the central hole?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately not,you can only resize whole model.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Qwarkk","CreatedById":154770,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-19T15:49:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222722131\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145972\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471595505\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002281294\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sebi.zzr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, sebi.zzr said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately not,you can only resize whole model.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought so, thanks anyway!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}